  "text": "Simultaneously a [6,6-2 H 2 ]glucose solution was infused in order to maintain euglycaemia. To monitor blood glucose levels during the clamp study, arterialised venous blood was taken at 5-min intervals from a retrograde cannula on the dorsum of the right hand, which was warmed. The mean glucose infusion rate between 80 and 120 min after commencement of the insulin infusion was calculated. The glucose disposal rate was calculated after correction for residual hepatic glucose production using the [6,6-2 H 2 ]glucose tracer [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
